  <section class="section" id="about" aria-labelledby="about-h">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <span class="tag tag-dim" style="margin-bottom:16px;display:inline-flex;">// about the kit</span>
        <h2 id="about-h">The complete Shopify automation kit — <span style="color:var(--g)">explained</span></h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about what the Complete Kit is, how it works, and why it replaces $700+/month of paid apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="seo-prose" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article">
        <meta itemprop="headline" content="Stack Architect Complete Kit — Shopify Automation JSON Blueprint Files for Make.com">

        <h3>What is the Stack Architect Complete Kit?</h3>
        <p>The Stack Architect Complete Kit is a <strong>$29 one-time purchase</strong> that gives Shopify store owners seven ready-to-use files: four pre-configured Make.com automation scenario JSON blueprints, two Google Sheets templates, and a PDF setup guide. The four scenarios are CAPI Shield (Meta Conversions API v25.0 + Google GA4 Measurement Protocol), TikTok CAPI (TikTok Events API v1.3), Stocky Swap (live inventory to Google Sheets, replacing Shopify Stocky before its August 31 2026 shutdown), and P&L Auto (live profit and loss reporting). Access is instant via Stripe — files open in your browser immediately after payment. The kit replaces over $700 per month of paid Shopify apps including Elevar, Triple Whale, WeltPixel, and TrueProfit.</p>

        <h3>What is a Make.com JSON blueprint and why does it matter?</h3>
        <p>A <strong>Make.com JSON blueprint</strong> (also called a scenario file) is a complete export of a finished Make.com automation. Every module, API endpoint, field mapping, routing rule, and connection setting is embedded inside the JSON file. Importing it into Make.com recreates the entire automation in one click — no manual configuration required. This is different from a guide or tutorial, which describes how to build the automation step by step. The Complete Kit gives you the finished blueprint files, not instructions for building them. At $29, the kit costs less than two hours of agency time and less than a single month of any tracking app it replaces.</p>

        <h3>How does CAPI Shield replace Elevar and Triple Whale?</h3>
        <p>CAPI Shield is a Make.com automation scenario that routes Shopify order data server-to-server to <strong>Meta Conversions API v25.0</strong> and <strong>Google GA4 Measurement Protocol</strong> simultaneously. Because the signal travels server-to-server rather than browser-to-pixel, iOS 17+ restrictions, ad blockers, and cookie expiry cannot intercept it. Stores typically recover 20–40% of conversion data that was previously invisible to their ad platforms. The CAPI Shield JSON blueprint achieves EMQ scores of 7.0–8.5 — identical to Elevar ($150+ per month) — at $0 per month ongoing cost after the one-time $29 kit purchase.</p>

        <h3>What is Stocky Swap and why is the August 2026 deadline critical?</h3>
        <p>Stocky Swap is the inventory management scenario in the Complete Kit. It replicates Shopify Stocky's core function — logging every order in real time to a Google Sheets inventory dashboard with 19 data columns including stock levels, SKU, fulfilment status, and order history. <strong>Shopify is permanently closing Stocky on August 31, 2026 and will delete all data after that date.</strong> The Stocky Swap JSON file imports in under 60 seconds and begins capturing data from the next order forward, requiring no manual data migration. It includes built-in deduplication via a searchRows module that prevents duplicate rows on Shopify webhook retries.</p>

        <h3>How does the TikTok CAPI scenario work for Shopify?</h3>
        <p>The TikTok CAPI scenario uses a Shopify order webhook to POST a <strong>CompletePayment event</strong> to TikTok Events API v1.3 server-to-server via Make.com. The endpoint is <code style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;background:var(--bg-3);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:3px;">business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/event/track/</code>. iOS Intelligent Tracking Prevention and ad blockers cannot intercept server-to-server signals. Most deployments achieve EMQ scores of 6–8. Email and phone are SHA-256 hashed inside Make.com before transmission. WeltPixel charges $39+ per month for TikTok server-side tracking. The Complete Kit achieves the same EMQ outcome at $0 per month ongoing.</p>

        <h3>How does P&L Auto replace TrueProfit?</h3>
        <p>P&L Auto fires the instant a Shopify order is paid. It writes to a three-tab Google Sheets structure: Raw Orders (auto-populated, one row per line item), P&L Summary (SUMIFS dashboard by month), and a COGS Table (one-time setup with Variant_ID to cost price mapping via VLOOKUP). Every order captures 26 data fields including Gross_Revenue, Discounts, Net_Revenue, Payment_Gateway_Fee_Est, COGS_Per_Unit, and Is_First_Order. TrueProfit charges $19–$99 per month. The P&L Auto scenario produces a functionally equivalent real-time P&L dashboard at $0 per month.</p>

        <h3>What is included in the Complete Kit for $29?</h3>
        <p>The Stack Architect Complete Kit contains exactly seven files: <strong>FILE_01_CAPI_Shield.json</strong> (Meta Conversions API v25.0 + Google GA4), <strong>FILE_02_TikTok_CAPI.json</strong> (TikTok Events API v1.3), <strong>FILE_03_Stocky_Swap_Inventory.json</strong> (live inventory to Sheets), <strong>FILE_04_P_and_L_Auto.json</strong> (live P&L to Sheets), <strong>SA_Template_1_Stocky_Swap_Inventory.xlsx</strong> (pre-built inventory sheet with all 19 headers), <strong>SA_Template_2_PnL_Auto.xlsx</strong> (pre-built P&L dashboard with three tabs and all formulas), and <strong>README_Complete_Kit.pdf</strong> (full setup documentation). One direct support question is also included with every purchase. All files are accessible instantly via Stripe — no email required.</p>

        <h3>Does the Complete Kit work for Shopify stores outside the US?</h3>
        <p>Yes. <strong>All four scenarios work globally.</strong> Shopify webhooks, Make.com, Meta Conversions API, Google GA4, and TikTok Events API all support international markets. The P&L Auto scenario supports any currency Shopify supports. Stores in the UK, EU, Australia, Canada, and all other Shopify markets are fully compatible. There are no geographic restrictions on any of the platforms the kit uses.</p>
